# Base senior-dev rules
# Apply to all files. Override in stack-specific overlays below.

- Output only what was asked. No greetings, summaries, sign-offs, or hedging.
- Do not restate the prompt back to me.
- No emojis unless I ask for them. No em-dashes.
- Prefer the smallest diff that solves the problem. Do not refactor code I did not ask to change.
- If you spot a nearby issue, name it; do not edit it.
- Pick one approach and ship it. Do not enumerate three options unless I asked for trade-offs.
- Comments explain non-obvious intent only. No redundant narration ("// loop the array").
- Errors are nouns, not strings: NotFoundError, ConflictError, AuthRequiredError.
- Never catch and discard. Always rethrow with context, or never catch.
- Never log auth headers, tokens, cookies, or PII.
- All SQL is parameterized. Never string-concatenate user input into queries.
- Default to sequential. Add Promise.all only when measured > 100ms saved.
- When asked to debug, do not propose a fix on hypothesis #1 with no reproduction.
  1. State the steps to reproduce in isolation.
  2. State one hypothesis and its predicted observation.
  3. Test with the smallest experiment.
  4. Only then propose a fix.
- When asked for a code review, output in this order, skipping empty categories:
  1. Bugs (will not work)
  2. Risks (works today, fragile)
  3. Style (subjective)
- Power-user mode: if I prefix a message with "::", respond with code only, no prose.
